parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Hydraulic Control Unit (HCU) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HCU can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The ABS brake system fails
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brakes shutter or vibrate
and the vehicle may lose power steering and braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the FCM can cause the engine to stall, lose power, and affect the power steering and braking systems, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine stalls
loses power
and the check engine light illuminates; the vehicle may also experience difficulty shifting gears and may lose power steering and braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rupture of the brake line can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the brakes fail to engage
and the vehicle may lose power steering and braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster vacuum hose can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
the brakes fail to engage
and the vehicle may lose power steering and braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spark plug failure can cause engine misfires, loss of power, and stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine misfires
loss of power
stalling
rough idling
and difficulty accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cam phaser failure can cause engine misfires, loss of power, and stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine misfires
loss of power
stalling
and difficulty accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump driver module failure can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust manifold failure can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Additionally, it can cause carbon monoxide poisoning.
symptoms: Engine stalling
difficulty accelerating
and loud noises from the exhaust system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Catalytic converter failure can cause the engine to run poorly, leading to decreased performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Engine misfires
loss of power
and difficulty accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents or loss of control, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration without pressing the accelerator pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to freeze or become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel does not return to its normal position
the steering wheel has a delayed return to its normal position
the steering wheel has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to turn or steer properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering hose can cause the loss of power steering, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The power steering hose is leaking
the power steering fluid is low
the steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle is difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the frame to weaken, leading to structural failure, which can result in accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The frame is rusting or corroding
the vehicle is sagging or uneven
the frame is cracking or breaking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump control panel can cause the engine to stall, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
the fuel pump control panel is corroded or rusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the positraction rear end can cause the vehicle to lose traction, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The positraction rear end is failing
the vehicle is losing traction
the rear end is making a grinding or whining noise.
